goals.question: What is the distribution of miles driven by side of the road?

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='miles', y='gas')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between miles driven and gas consumption?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    yearly_gas = data.groupby('year')['gas'].mean().reset_index()
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='gas', data=yearly_gas)
    plt.title('What is the average gas consumption per year?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
